istic forenames:  Irish Brendan.","Irish (Galway and Mayo; Wexford): Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Ceanndubháin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Ceanndubhán</i>’, a byname meaning ‘little black-headed one’, from <i>ceann</i> ‘head’ + <i>dubh</i> ‘black’ + the diminutive suffix <i>-án</i>."]},{"name":"Whitted","meanings":["Scottish: probably a shortened form of   Whitehead  ."]},{"name":"Whittet","meanings":["Scottish (Perthshire and Angus): variant of   Whitehead  . Compare   Whitted  ."]},{"name":"Whited","meanings":["Shortened form of English   Whitehead  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1647029,"age":0,"year":"1783","julianDay":2372288,"title":"A Free America","description":"The Revolutionary War ended with the signing of the Treaty of Paris which gave the new nation boundries on which they could expand and trade with other countries without any problems.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1783)","urlTitle":"The New Treaty of Paris","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1647030,"age":3,"year":"1786","julianDay":2373384,"title":"Shays' Rebellion","description":"Caused by war veteran Daniel Shays, Shays' Rebellion was to protest economic and civil rights injustices that he and other farmers were seeing after the Revolutionary War. Because of the Rebellion it opened the eyes of the governing officials that the Articles of Confederation needed a reform. The Rebellion served as a guardrail when helping reform the United States Constitution.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/early-us/shays-rebellion","urlTitle":"Shays' Rebellion","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1677767,"age":13,"year"